transmission.description: Due to transmission issues, the John Deere 8010s were returned to the factory and converted into 8020s. One 8010 escaped the recall and is currently in the Keller collection.
The 8020 was introduced after problems occurred with the 8010. The 8020s were model 8010 tractors rebuilt with a new transmission.
The Kubota L4300 was an "economy" version of the L4310. It was only available with an unsynchronized 8-speed gear transmission and no cab was offered.
The Kubota MX5000 was marketed as an intermediate model between the L and M series line. It was less expensive than the similar M4900 and used a more basic transmission and hydraulic system.

The New Holland TC25D was available only in four-wheel drive and with the hydrostatic transmission.
The Hydra-Power transmission offered an under-drive to each drive gear, which could be selected on the move. The Hydraul-Shift offered and on-the-fly under- and over-drive gear.
The optional Hydraul-Shift transmission allows the operator to shift on the move to an over- or under-drive for each drive gear.
The Ford 941 Powermaster was the only model in the row-crop 901 series to have the four-speed transmission.
Advertised as the Case 400 Case-O-Matic, the Case 410B was an upgraded version of the Case 300 utility with the new Case-O-Matic torque converter transmission.
Advertised as the Case 400 Case-O-Matic, the Case 411B was an upgraded version of the Case 300 row-crop with the new Case-O-Matic torque converter transmission.
A high-speed fourth gear was optional in most 630 series transmissions, an H would appear at the end of the model number to inidcate this option.
B.F. Avery Louisville Motor Plow Transmission
The County 1164 was based on the gearbox and transmission from the Ford 5000 and the engine from the Ford 8000.
